  "learn": {
    "heading": "Comparing with < and >",
    "intro": "<p>An <strong>inequality</strong> compares two amounts that may not be equal. <strong>&lt;</strong> means \"less than\" and <strong>&gt;</strong> means \"greater than.\" The wide open end points to the bigger number.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>3 &lt; 7</strong> reads \"3 is less than 7.\" <strong>9 &gt; 2</strong> reads \"9 is greater than 2.\"",
      "Words to symbols: \"more than\" → <strong>&gt;</strong>, \"less than\" → <strong>&lt;</strong>. So \"a number greater than 5\" is <strong>n &gt; 5</strong>."
    ]
  },
